texts.text: >In an abandoned ruin somewhere in town...
Umm, Megakin. Is this really the place?
That's what Seiran told me.
But this place is so creepy Shiang Sun's literally dancing with joy.
Hey, that's not true.
Yes I am excited, but I'm not dancing!
So you ARE excited...
Oh, you're here. Yoo-hoo!
Thank god you're here.
What are we doing here anyway?
Oh, what's wrong? Don't tell me you were scared?
Well, sorry for calling you all out here, but there's an emergency.
So, what kind of Dragon Stream problem is it this time?
Nice try... But this time, I think it's something...
Something far worse.
You all know about the strange disappearances that's been all over the news lately, right?
Oh, is that the one where people disappear after saying
they're leaving for a utopia where their talents will be appreciated?
That's the one. This may have something to do with it.
It may not look it, but this place is actually a portal of sorts to the Aura Gate...
In other words, it borders between our world and the spirit world.
Is that why it's so creepy?
Maybe. But anyway, what happened was
a new Aura Gate popped up here,
and the people who disappeared are all inside.
That about explains it.
Wait, how can you be sure they're the people that disappeared?
I was here to investigate the new Aura Gate, and found that it had visitors.
I recognized a few of them because their faces were on the news.
They went in, and never came out.
So for some reason they went into this spirit place and couldn't get out?
Most likely yes. That's why we need to go in and investigate.
How?
So we just waltz in?
It's just like any other Aura Gate.
You can't just walk in. I'll have to take you inside.

Okay, just close your eyes now.
Feel the flow of your chi.
...Good. We're inside
When you said Aura Gate, I imagined something more outlandish. But this...
We're inside a normal building... right?
Yes... This is astounding. Now that we're seeing this from the inside, it's perfectly clear.
This is our world. We're seeing what is supposed to be in this location in our world.
At the same time, this is just like an Aura Gate.
There's energy everywhere, and spiritual interference.
It's as if the real world is being corroded by the spiritual one, and the two are sort of fused together because of it.
Yoyoyo, why is this happenin―
Wait, someone's coming.
G-Get away!
It's too strong! How're we supposed to beat this thing!
Garr...!
Those two are being attacked by a demon! We have to help!
Damn you! If it weren't for my injuries, I'd fu―

Karma... Power...
Give me...!!
Aaaargh!!
Oh my god!
God... dammit...
>The man falls to his knees, and then collapses.
>The fallen man's body disappears, leaving some strange crystals scattered on the floor.
There's still one left! We have to save him!
Devil Download!
Thanks for saving my life...
Don't mention it. I'm glad you're okay.
No, I mean it. You people saw what happened right?
That demon killed that guy and took his Blood Karma.
If it weren't for you, I'd have ended up the same...
Blood Karma...? Do you mean those red crystal things?
Yes, they're like crystalized life force.
You can get them by killing someone, and consume them to become more powerful.
K-Killing someone? How can you take that so lightly―
So you seem to know a lot about this place. Can you tell us what you know?
Yes, of course. You guys saved my life. It's the least I could do.
From what I heard, this world was created by demons.
You know, the ones with 3 faces and 6 arms? The Asuras, that's what they're called.
They said that here, power is everything.
There are no rules to bind us. We can get whatever we want by force.
They told us to fight and take Blood Karma from others, so we would become strong.
They want you to grow strong in a world where power is everything? Why would they want that?
Beats me. Maybe there's a reason for all this, but I don't know what it is.
Oh, I've also heard that aside from the Asuras,
other powerful beings also exist in this world.
But since I've never met any of them, I have no idea what they're like...
That's about all I know.
Thank you. You've been a great help.
But how, may I ask, did you manage to come here in the first place?
Normally, people should not be able to enter a place like this.
You're right. This is a utopia where only the chosen few can come!
So what happened was, one day I suddenly started to hear this voice in my head.
At the time I thought I was going crazy...
but I think it actually meant that I was "chosen".
So I followed the directions given to me by this voice to this location, and I entered this world.
Okay... Maybe it was someone on the inside that guided you here...?
But let's put that mystery aside for now. What's important here is that this place is not safe.
There are no laws here, only chaos. It's a no man's land.
So you should go back to the real world, understand?
B-But!
You almost died back there! Please, just do as I say.
...Alright.
Good thing he listened to reason.
We can't investigate this place with him in tow now, can we?
So... What do we do next?
Oh, about that.
My senses tell me that the energy that make up this world
and Blood Karma are basically the same.
This is only a theory, but...
If the spiritual energy that makes up this world is the same thing as the Blood Karma,
we might be able to stop this world from corroding our own by disposing of this Karma.
And if that proves to be the case, we should also be able to diminish or even eliminate this world.
Wow! You can sense all that? That's amazing! Can I call you Madame Seiran from now on?
Impressive, right? Yes. Madame Seiran is, in fact, deceptively brilliant.
You show a lot of confidence, even though it's just a "theory".
Wouldn't it be kind of embarrassing if your theory turns out to be wrong?

I... don't think it will!
Don't think! Feel!
Well, since we've got nothin' else to go on, we'll just have to try out this theory!
Explore buildings. Find demons. Collect Blood Karma. Simple enough!
I'm thankful for being saved...
But there's no place for me in the real world.
That's why I came here in the first place.
This place is the only hope I have left.
So...
>The man steps into the ruins once more...
